Our writer gets into the Halloween spirit by scaring herself silly on a Hound of the Baskervilles tour, exploring the bleak landscapes that inspired Sir Arthur Conan Doyle’s novel

The wind is howling as I peer through the mist at a particularly bleak bit of Dartmoor, trying not to let my boots sink into the thick, black mud. I’m on the edge of swampy, fog-shrouded Fox Tor Mire, which was the inspiration for Grimpen
